title: AARVEX NVIDIA Graphic Card GT610 2GB DDR3 2 GB DDR3 Gra...
Sales Package: The AARVEX GT610 2GB is an entry-level graphics card, often used for basic computing tasks, light multimedia applications, and very casual gaming., The AARVEX GT610 2GB is not designed for gaming. It can handle very light gaming or older titles, but it's primarily intended for improving visual performance in basic tasks, such as video playback and desktop applications., For multimedia use, it can accelerate HD video decoding and provide a smoother experience compared to integrated graphics., It is also a good choice for upgrading an older system that lacks any form of discrete GPU, providing a noticeable performance boost over integrated solutions in certain scenarios.
Graphics Technologies Supported: Microsoft DirectX v11, Open GL Optimization v4.2, No support
DVI and HDMI Interface: 1 x DVI Output Out, Yes x Dual Link DVI Out, 1 x HDMI Output Out, The AARVEX GT610 2GB usually includes a DVI to VGA adapter and possibly an HDMI to DVI adapter. These adapters help connect the card to different types of monitors and displays. Always verify the included items with the specific package you purchase.
Other Interface: Yes x Co-Axial TV Out, No x VIVO Out, 3 x Display Port Out, In addition to HDMI, DVI, and VGA outputs, the AARVEX GT610 2GB provides features like HDMI audio output, support for multi-monitor setups, and compatibility with various adapters. It also supports HDCP for protected content playback. The NVIDIA Control Panel is used for configuring and managing these connectivity options.
Cooling and Heatsink: The AARVEX GT610 2GB usually uses a passive cooling solution with a heatsink and no active fan. This design is aimed at providing silent operation but depends on good case airflow to manage heat effectively.
Additional Features: Video Playback: Enhances video playback quality with support for high-definition video formats. It includes hardware acceleration for video decoding, reducing CPU load during playback of HD video content., Parallel Computing: Supports CUDA (Compute Unified Device Architecture), allowing the GPU to perform general-purpose computing tasks in addition to graphics rendering. This can accelerate certain applications that are CUDA-enabled., 3D Support: While not a primary feature of the GT610, it is capable of supporting NVIDIA 3D Vision technology, which enables 3D gaming and multimedia experiences with the appropriate hardware and software., Driver Features: Includes features for performance tuning, overclocking, and other GPU management options through NVIDIA's GeForce drivers. The NVIDIA Control Panel allows for customization of graphics settings and display configurations., Extended Desktop: Supports multi-monitor setups, allowing for extended desktop environments across multiple screens using the available HDMI, DVI, and VGA outputs., Audio Integration: HDMI supports both video and audio, allowing for simplified connectivity with HDMI-compatible displays that support audio., Low Power Consumption: Designed to operate with low power consumption, making it suitable for systems with limited power supplies and contributing to overall energy efficiency., DirectX and OpenGL Support: Fully supports DirectX 11 and OpenGL 4.2, enabling compatibility with a wide range of applications and games that use these APIs.
Processors and Cores: 48 Stream Processor, 48 Shader Processors, 48 CUDA Cores
Shader: Shader Version 5 with Clock speed of 810 MHz
Supported OS: Potentially Windows 11, Windows 10, Windows 8.1 and 8, Windows 7, Windows XP
Software Included: The AARVEX GT610 2GB typically includes NVIDIA GeForce drivers, the NVIDIA Control Panel, and possibly NVIDIA GeForce Experience. Additional documentation and, in some cases, third-party software might also be included. It's important to check the contents of the specific package you receive, as software bundles can vary.
Other System Requirements: Minimum Power Supply: A minimum of 300 watts is generally recommended for the system. The GT610 has a low power consumption of about 29 watts, so it does not require additional power connectors beyond what the PCI Express slot provides., Slot Type: The card requires a PCI Express x16 slot on the motherboard. It is compatible with both PCIe 2.0 and 3.0 slots., Recommended RAM: At least 2 GB of system RAM is recommended to ensure smooth operation. More RAM may be needed depending on the system's overall configuration and the tasks being performed., Minimum CPU: A modern processor with at least 1.0 GHz or faster is recommended.
